text:
Since the port was upgraded to 91, it's no longer possible to subscribe to DAV calendars, since the password prompt never appears.
Already configured calendars keep working.

Steps to reproduce:
_ from "File" menu, choose "New" -> "Calendar";
_ in the dialog that appears choose "On the network" and press "Next";
_ fill "Username" and "Location" fields, the press "Find Calendars";
_ "Please wait while your calendars are being discovered" appears with a spinning wheel;
_ meanwhile a dialog asking for the password should appear, but it doesn't;
_ so only way out is to press "Cancel".

This is a FreeBSD specific problem, since the software works properly on Windows and Linux.
